The Nigerian Institute of Journalism (NIJ) has matriculated a total of 267 students to undergo courses in Mass Communication for its 2020/2021 academic session. Of the number, 68 are for the National Diploma (ND) programme, 96 for Higher National Diploma (HND), and 103 students for the Post Graduate Diploma (PGD) programme Speaking at the ceremony, the provost, Mr. Gbenga Adefaye reiterated the commitment of the school to providing the best learning environment for its students, including constant upgrade and acquisition of the state-of-the-art equipment and facilities to meet the current and future best practices. Adefaye said “At the NIJ, we strive to provide a most conducive learning environment as we constantly upgrade our equipment and facilities to meet the current and future best practices. We are unrelenting in our acquisition of the state-of-the-art facilities to deliver excellent training.” He said the school recently benefited from a digitisation support of the National Communication Commission (NCC) for seamless internet connectivity and cloud hosting, and that the upgrade on ICT centre was originally supported by the National Information Technology Development Agency (NITDA).